      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LUX AETERNA (9) is a quality mare who was tackling strong races before heading north and finding winning form last start by 3.2 metres at Albion Park. Starts alone on the back row and should have options from there. Take beating. SMIRKIN SERENE (6) resumes from a spell of three-and-a-half months after closing off last campaign in good form, scoring at her last appearance at Menangle. Has won when fresh before and has been readied with three nice trials. Expecting a bright start to the campaign. FARFALLA STRIDE (7) is hard to knock having made it three wins from her last four outings when coming from a similar barrier for a last-start win by a head at Menangle. Races well here with two wins and two placings from four attempts. PLATINUM JEWEL (8) was runner-up to LUX AETERNA last start and while she draws wide she had won two in a row in Brisbane prior so is going well.",
